WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.820
I’m in Shanghai visiting Alibaba’s new
retail concept store. The name? Hema.

00:00:05.820 --> 00:00:09.380
Not only is the tech titan
expanding into offline retail,

00:00:09.380 --> 00:00:13.780
but this location is the first with
its own robot restaurant too.

00:00:13.780 --> 00:00:18.200
Robots are actually delivering,
pretty much, all the food.

00:00:18.200 --> 00:00:21.800
That's where I’ll end up at after
the shopping experience.

00:00:21.800 --> 00:00:27.000
The Hema store is growing rapidly in
China, opening 65 locations in one year.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:31.200
There’s three pillars to its strategy:
serving as a place to shop in person,

00:00:31.200 --> 00:00:35.090
a distribution center for online
orders and the restaurant.

00:00:35.090 --> 00:00:39.280
It’s hoping to define what the
future of retail will look like.

00:00:39.280 --> 00:00:42.720
While I’m checking this out,
I might as well grab a basket.

00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:44.380
Let’s see what interests me.

00:00:44.380 --> 00:00:49.980
The first thing I notice is the pricing system. Every price
tag has a barcode, in which you can use the Hema app

00:00:49.980 --> 00:00:56.000
to scan the barcode and see the price of the item
online. You can also see reviews of that product.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.360
What’s also fascinating is that even though
these price tags look like they were printouts,

00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:04.020
it's a special technology that can
change the price in real-time.

00:01:04.020 --> 00:01:05.440
And that’s not all.

00:01:05.440 --> 00:01:09.400
It even tells you when it was delivered
to the store and where it came from.

00:01:09.400 --> 00:01:14.380
You can even see a scan of a government
certificate proving, for instance, if it was organic.

00:01:14.380 --> 00:01:18.660
It also shows delivery options if
you decide not to buy it in store.

00:01:18.660 --> 00:01:22.780
I just saw a lady who works for the store
and she was fulfilling an online order.

00:01:22.780 --> 00:01:26.840
So using her scanner, she had a
bag, she would pick the products.

00:01:26.840 --> 00:01:31.080
And then what was really crazy, is instead of walking
across the store to get it where it needs to go,

00:01:31.080 --> 00:01:37.980
she put it on a conveyer belt, which then took it to the
ceiling, to the back area, where it will go out for delivery.

00:01:37.980 --> 00:01:43.460
So essentially now you’re talking about not only
a retail store, but also a distribution center.

00:01:43.460 --> 00:01:46.480
And if you live within three
kilometers of a Hema store,

00:01:46.480 --> 00:01:49.940
you can have delivery of your
groceries within 30 minutes.

00:01:49.940 --> 00:01:54.180
You see a lot of employees walking
around the store, fulfilling orders.

00:01:54.180 --> 00:01:57.660
I understand how it can maximize
efficiency of sourcing,

00:01:57.660 --> 00:02:01.920
but it creates a somewhat chaotic experience too,
when you have a lot of people running around.

00:02:03.680 --> 00:02:06.000
A lot of sample stations
throughout the store.

00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:12.580
It's like a Costco. Sample
stations everywhere.

00:02:12.580 --> 00:02:15.380
At one point you ask yourself,
why even come to the store then?

00:02:15.380 --> 00:02:20.280
If everything is online and it's such an easy
experience to just order from an app.

00:02:20.280 --> 00:02:26.040
Well one reason Chinese consumers
prefer to come in store is for seafood.

00:02:26.040 --> 00:02:31.320
It's very important for the Chinese consumer to see
firsthand their seafood, to make sure it's fresh.

00:02:34.300 --> 00:02:36.840
Alright, so I picked two items
that I'm going to check out with.

00:02:36.840 --> 00:02:42.420
One of them is bananas, and the other one is
these Lays potato chips, Italian red meat flavor.

00:02:42.420 --> 00:02:44.060
Why not try something new?

00:02:44.060 --> 00:02:48.080
There’s literally no traditional
cashier at this grocery store.

00:02:48.080 --> 00:02:51.980
It's not like you have an option between
a cashier and self-checkout.

00:02:51.980 --> 00:02:55.320
So if you're looking for that human
interaction, go somewhere else.

00:02:55.320 --> 00:02:58.111
Using the Hema app, which
is connected to Alipay,

00:02:58.120 --> 00:03:02.480
consumers swipe their phone in front of
this scanner, and that’s pretty much it.

00:03:02.480 --> 00:03:06.240
There’s also the option to
pay using your face, too.

00:03:07.920 --> 00:03:10.220
And now, let me try those chips.

00:03:10.220 --> 00:03:13.340
It's actually a very subtle taste.
It's not too strong, surprisingly.

00:03:13.340 --> 00:03:15.580
Now, it’s time to try the robot restaurant.

00:03:15.580 --> 00:03:20.440
To get a table here, you can check in at
a kiosk, you guessed it, using the app.

00:03:20.440 --> 00:03:25.600
It's connected to your identity, your name, everything
you've bought in the past, and of course, your wallet.

00:03:25.600 --> 00:03:30.780
From there, you get assigned a table. Once you're
assigned a table, you scan the barcode at the table.

00:03:30.780 --> 00:03:34.700
And then from there, you can just start
placing your order on the Hema app.

00:03:36.840 --> 00:03:40.780
So you’re not waiting for anyone to come take
your order. There's no pen or paper, any of that.

00:03:40.780 --> 00:03:44.260
In fact, you really have no
interaction with a staff member.

00:03:44.260 --> 00:03:47.120
And then from there, the
robots deliver your food.

00:03:47.120 --> 00:03:49.980
And you've already paid,
all within the same app.

00:03:49.980 --> 00:03:55.240
Alibaba leveraged its existing technology
from the e-commerce automated warehouses

00:03:55.240 --> 00:03:57.960
to power these new robot restaurants.

00:03:57.960 --> 00:04:04.460
It's really an entire ecosystem of robots that are working
together pretty well. I have yet to see a collision.

00:04:04.460 --> 00:04:08.080
Even the tablet at the
table, in a way, is obsolete.

00:04:08.080 --> 00:04:13.840
The only thing the tablet can really do is entertain you.
There's games, which your phone probably has.

00:04:13.840 --> 00:04:17.140
You can call for a server if you
need, you can use the tablet for that.

00:04:17.140 --> 00:04:20.260
And then there's also a demo of
how the robots work as well.

00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:23.165
The robots can't handle
everything though.

00:04:23.165 --> 00:04:27.920
For complicated dishes, like soups,
that'll require a human server.

